comment.undefined: The WINGS ComponentArgument is a WINGS component class that represents a componentArgument in the  WINGS Workflow template specification.
The WINGS Component is a WINGS component class that represents a component of WINGS Workflow template specification.
The WINGS ParameterArgument is a WINGS component class that represents a parameter based argument and it has the Component argument as a subclass.
The WINGS DataArgument is a WINGS component class that represents a data based argument and it has the Component argument as a subclass.
The WINGS hasDimensionSizes is a WINGS workflow component data property that represents a WingsWorkflowComponentArgument having dimensional sizes (specified as a string) for its componentArgument.
The WINGS hasDocumentation is a WINGS workflow component data property that represents a WingsWorkflowComponent having a documentation for its component.

The WINGS hasOutput is a WINGS workflow component object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflowComponent and the component's data argument i.e. a WingsWorkflowComponent hasOutput a WingsWorkflowDataArgument.
The WINGS hasRule is a WINGS workflow component data property that represents a WingsWorkflowComponent having a rule (specified as a block of code in strings) for its component.

The WINGS hasInput is a WINGS workflow component object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflowComponent and the component's argument i.e. a WingsWorkflowComponent hasInput a WingsWorkflowComponentArgument.
The WINGS hasArgumentIndex is a WINGS workflow component data property that represents a WingsWorkflowComponent having a argumentIndex (specified as a number(int) eg. 0,1,2,...) for its component.
The WINGS isInvalid is a WINGS workflow component data property that represents a WingsWorkflowComponent is either valid or not.
The WINGS hasArgumentID is a WINGS workflow component data property that represents a WingsWorkflowComponent having a argumentID (specified as string) for its component.

The WINGS isConcrete is a WINGS workflow component data property that represents a WingsWorkflowComponent is abstract or not. If it is abstract then the value is false, else its true. (range is boolean)
The WINGS hasValue is a WINGS workflow component data property that represents a WingsWorkflowComponentParameterArgument having a value for the parameter.
The WINGS hasArgumentName is a WINGS workflow component data property that represents a WingsWorkflowComponent having a argumentName (specified as a string) for its component.

The WINGS hasArgument is a WINGS workflow component object property that represents a connection between a WingsWorkflowComponent and the component's argument i.e. a WingsWorkflowComponent hasArgument a WingsWorkflowComponentArgument.
The WINGS hasBindingID is a WINGS workflow component data property that represents a WingsWorkflowComponentArgument having a ID (specified as a string) for its componentArgument.
The WINGS hasLocation is a WINGS workflow component data property that represents a WingsWorkflowComponent having a location (specified as a string) for its component.

The WINGS hasDimensionIndexProperties is a WINGS workflow component data property that represents a WingsWorkflowComponentArgument having dimensional properties (specified as a string) for its componentArgument.
The WINGS hasDimensionality is a WINGS workflow component data property that represents a WingsWorkflowComponentArgument having dimensionality (specficied as a number(int) 0,1).
